item.title: Purdue ROV (Remotely Operated Underwater Vehicle)
item.description:
This semester I joined the Purdue ROV team. This student-led team builds an Underwater Robot that performs tasks to protect the ocean’s ecosystem. These tasks are stuipulated by the MATE ROV competition, a yearly World Championship that we take part in over the summer.

This year, the competition is in Newfoundland & Labrador, Canada and to go with the theme with the location, our robot should be able to handle low temperatures in an ice tank, high water velocities in a flume tank, and saltwater in an offshore engineering basin.
